value.title: Kamala Harris pays tribute to RBG with Supreme Court pic
value.excerpt: Democratic Vice Presidential candidate Kamala Harris paid tribute to the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsberg Saturday, calling the liberal icon a “titan.”

value.title: Susan Collins says Trump can nominate a justice, but Senate vote should wait until after election
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Susan Collins on Saturday weighed in on the US Supreme Court vacancy, saying that she believes waiting until after the election is the right decision.

value.title: Trump Describes Journalist Hit By Rubber Bullet ‘A Beautiful Sight’
value.excerpt: At a rally in Minnesota, President Trump described an MSNBC anchor hit by a rubber bullet while covering protests after the death of George Floyd in May as “a beautiful sight,” comments quickly condemned by journalists including CNN’s Jake Tapper.

value.title: Sen. Thune says Trump's Supreme Court nominee 'will receive a vote'
value.excerpt: Thune's statement Friday night was a shift from his position after Justice Antonin Scalia died in February 2016, leaving a Supreme Court vacancy.

value.title: Trump urges GOP to move 'without delay' as he ponders impact of Supreme Court on election
value.excerpt: Trump is considering a woman for his latest Supreme Court nominee, aides said, and expects to make the Supreme Court a major campaign issue.

value.title: Speak Out reader opinion: Trump is not listening to scientists on climate change

value.title: Evangelicals at base of Trump hopes for Pennsylvania repeat
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump’s homestretch push to repeat his razor thin victory in Pennsylvania four years ago won't happen without white evangelicals, and there are signs that critical component of his coalition hasn't lost the faith.

value.title: Behind Trump's Turkish 'bromance': Lev Parnas, oligarchs and a lucrative lobbying deal
value.excerpt: Turkey’s effort to influence the Trump White House began at the Watergate, in a meeting brokered by a figure from the Ukraine impeachment saga, Lev Parnas.

value.title: Ginsburg vacancy puts pressure on Trump-critic Republicans in Senate
value.excerpt: Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg’s death Friday has put a spotlight on a handful of unpredictable Republican senators.

value.title: Current events: Electric fence deters Trump sign thieves
value.excerpt: A Massachusetts man tired of people stealing his Donald Trump campaign sign has come up with a shocking solution: an electrified fence

value.title: AP-NORC poll: Trump faces deep pessimism as election nears
value.excerpt: Most Americans are deeply pessimistic about the direction of the country and skeptical of President Donald Trump’s handling of the coronavirus pandemic

value.title: Joe Biden mourns Ruth Bader Ginsburg and says she shouldn't be replaced until after the election
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee and former Vice President Joe Biden mourned the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg on Friday and demanded that voters dictate the next president before her replacement is chosen.

value.title: Rep. Engel agrees to drop Pompeo subpoena now that he has Biden documents
value.excerpt: House Foreign Affairs Chairman Eliot Engel on Friday agreed to withdraw a subpoena he had issued in July against Secretary of State Mike Pompeo after the State Department turned over more than 16,000 pages of documents the committee had sought, the panel announced.

value.title: Trump Says Confederate General Robert E. Lee 'Would Have Won Except for Gettysburg'
value.excerpt: "They're ripping down our history," President Donald Trump said of U.S. protesters. "That's where these guys begin. They take away your history."

value.title: Who is Amy Coney Barrett, the judge Trump has considered for a Supreme Court seat
value.excerpt: Barrett was floated by Trump as a possible replacement for Justice Ruth Bader Ginsberg in 2019 to associates.

value.title: Trump said he 'did not like' FBI Director Wray's testimony on Russia election meddling
value.excerpt: In congressional testimony on Thursday, Wray said that, as in 2016, Russia remains "very active" in efforts to "influence our election."

value.title: Trump announces aid for Puerto Rico, infusing politics in an apparent play for Florida voters
value.excerpt: Polling shows Trump and Biden are tied in Florida, where thousands of Puerto Ricans relocated after Hurricane Maria.

value.title: Trump on whether FBI Director Wray could be replaced: 'We're looking at a lot of different things'
value.excerpt: The president ripped Wray for his comments regarding Russian election interference and Antifa.

value.title: White House tries to play defense with falsehoods about former Pence aide Troye
value.excerpt: The White House moved quickly Thursday to try to discredit Olivia Troye, the former aide to Vice President Mike Pence, after she released a video charging that President Donald Trump failed to protect the public from coronavirus and that he only cared about getting reelected.

value.title: Kosovo gives Trump Order of Freedom for his role in securing deal with Serbia
value.excerpt: Kosovo gave President Trump one of its highest honors on Friday for his role in an historic economic normalization deal with Serbia earlier this month.

value.title: Trump vows enough coronavirus vaccine doses for ‘every American’ by April
value.excerpt: President Trump, during a White House press conference on Friday, said the United States will produce enough coronavirus vaccine doses for “every American” by April.
